modules.description: This module enables geolocation-based lookups to retrieve country identifiers (codes, names) and geographic metadata from IP addresses (IPv4/IPv6) or domain names, using a preloaded database handle. It operates on structured handles referencing GeoIP databases, supporting queries via IP strings, raw integers, or hostnames, alongside database metadata inspection. Typical applications include localization, regional analytics, and security systems requiring IP-to-country mapping with customizable database sources.
